commit.message: Typo fixed. [skip ci]

Use a standard function for temp files, secure permissions.

(Autosaved) temporary files now use a wxWidgets standard
function (CreateTempFileName) for the name generation instead
of using the process id as 'random' number.

Create the autosaved files with secure permissions: read- and
writeable only for the owner.

If the document has not title, save it as m_tempfileName.

This prevents a popup error message after a few minutes,
if the user has modified a new worksheet but not saved it under
a name, that the file could not be renamed (to an empty file,
that will of course fail).

Output a different error message with the reason why wxm files could not be read.

Is it a permission problem, or is the file format issue?

Maybe we must introduce something like version 2 of WXM in the future
(issue #1907)?
If MSVC likes this more?

commit.message: Manual: More wxm documentation.
Manual: Add documentation of the wxm file format.
Merge branch 'main' of github.com:wxMaxima-developers/wxmaxima into main

Prevent unneeded compiling of source files.

Now we create "*.h.tmp" files and 'copy_if_different' them to
the "*.h" files afterwards.
This prevents compiling several source files if one does

cmake <path-to-source>
make

twice (without changing any source files). Or if source files are
changed, only the changed source files are recompiled, not several
others too (because included header files got a new timestamp).
Paranoia: Make cells in the evaluation queue read NULL if they disappeared
